hey i'm having a weird issue with this c++ snippet in my embedded project. the heap just keeps growing and growing until the device crashes. i'm using new/delete but i can't see where i'm messing up. can u take a look?

```cpp
void processSensorData(int sensorId) {
    int* dataBuffer = new int[100];

    if (sensorId < 0) {
        return; 
    }

    for (int i = 0; i < 100; ++i) {
        dataBuffer[i] = readSensor(sensorId, i);
    }

    // do something with data
    storeData(dataBuffer);

    delete[] dataBuffer;
}
```
it looks okay to me but it's definitely leaking. why is the memory not being freed?

